race.comment: SENTIMENTAL LEGEND (3) was back and caught wide from the 15 barrier and made a big impression on debut when winning his Maiden easily this track/distance. Resumes today and has switched from the Williams yard. Draws out but Pike stays aboard suggesting he's pleasing the new camp. He will take plenty of beating on what we've seen. MASMELO (9) resumes and can threaten if presented on song. Was last seen at Group 3 level over a mile and before that won an Ascot Maiden by almost five lengths over 1800m. Resumes in much easier grade this time around and brings a sharp 1000m trial from Belmont. Finally draws a low barrier and Chris Parnham's booking is a decent push for her chances. ICANDOIT ONMYOWN (11) improved again when beaten 1L this track/trip in a CL3. Races forward and can get some of the cash. AURORA QUEEN (4) rates similarly on her near miss in a CL1 this track/trip. Has CJP in the saddle and look for her to present late.
